$interpreted: Elio: Today...it's the serious princess...
Hooligan Goon: The stuff you sold us is defective. Are you going to compensate me or not!
Sherlock: ... Hoho, I was being nice, yet you think I'm really that clueless? You're hired by the treasure shop on the corner to cause me trouble!
Sherlock: What, getting antsy because the elections are near? Trying to take my position as vice president of the Commerce Chamber, yet using such lowly tactics?
Hooligan Leader: Hmph, if you can't understand words, then perhaps fists will do the trick. Boys, let's turn this tin can into scrap metal!
Sherlock: Man, you hired folks sure know how to take your sweet time!
Sherlock: Now get them!
Hooligan Leader: Damn it! This tin can has got hidden helpers! Wreck them!
Naya: You stinkin robot, how dare you use Angel as your meat shield! I'm going to strip you down to a junk pile!
Sherlock: If "bodyguards" can't protect the princess, it's on you.
Sherlock: Why are you acting surprised? The Atlas incident was a continent-level mega deal. I already knew who all you people were.
Sherlock: BUT, I'm a nice and sensible guy. I won't be a big mouth...
Sherlock: What, are you here to honor your promises and give me the treasure we agreed on?
Angelia: No, I'm here to request your help for something else...
Naya: Also, for that promise you mentioned, didn't we fulfill it by getting the Rainbow Roses for you?
Sherlock: The Rainbow Roses wee compensation for me selling out Theodore. Telling you his purchase of the Rayzor blueprints, totally different matter!
Elio: Wow, so such penny-pinching people really do exist...
Sherlock: Where did you get this little wimp? Keep your mouth shut while we adults talk business.
Sherlock: All in all, before I get the rewards you promised, no deal! Leave, now!
Angelia: If we want to get down to the minute details, then what about those goons we just took care for you? Does that count towards the deal as well?
Sherlock: Umm..that's...
Angelia: Also, I heard Sir mentioning the election and the vice president position. I believe it's about the Bazaar's Commerce Chamber, right?
Angelia: If so, how about we discuss another deal?
Sherlock: Whaddaya mean?
Angelia: We outsiders will take care of those who threaten your position and ensure that your position as the vice president is stable. Is that fine with you?
Sherlock: My, my, princess darling, you are very different compared to the first time we met...
Angelia: I take that as an agreement to what I just proposed?
Sherlock: The election is tomorrow. There will be a group of folks entering from the East entrance. They are the ones who are trying to take my position.
Sherlock: As long as you keep them out of the Bazaar before sunset, I'll accept any request you have.
Angelia: Understood. We will honor our promises. Naya, Elio, we shall leave here first.
Sherlock: Deal confirmed. On a side note, the female leading that group is seriously bad news. Make sure you show no mercy!
